review_text:
Everything was great. The roast duck was a fat one, very well sliced before your eyes, the skin and fat clearly apart from the flesh. You can well adjust the content of your pancake to your taste. I have enjoyed this duck a great deal. And i was not alone, many chinese people seemed to be enjoy it as well....

We found it with no hope, just attracted by the front window and we had a very pleasant time. We tried tofu Plate and noodles with vegetables. And good desert as well ! The yellow tea is served for free. We recommend !

Surrounded by many Peking duck restaurants scattered all over Beijing, Siji Minfu serves good peking duck at a reasonable price...
